Establishment of an information access center consisting of informatization education centers, Internet lounges, seminar rooms, operator's offices, etc. in developing countries;

Information Access Center (IAC) is a Multi-functional facility that includes ICT Training Lab, ICT Complex Room, Seminar Room, and Administrative office. NIA provides IT infrastructure equipped with the newest PCs, A/Vs, O/As. etc, along with the general interior design/ construction of the center through the IAC Project. The Project aims to offer local communities a wide range of opportunities for ICT enablement and to bring them into Information Society, thus contributing to bridging the Global Digital Divide.

Aimed to bridge the digital divide and strengthen teacher and students' ICT in education capacities through the use of a digital classroom powered by solar panels which are immediately applicable in environments that lack sustainable electricity and educational infrastructure, in addition to local and international teacher training programmes led by Korean and international ICT in education specialists

Government officials and village leaders are invited to Korea and learn about agricultural village/local development theories, have on-site trainings and make action plans, in order to make a self-reliant local community.

A policy consulting project consisted of joint research with partner countries and international organizations, online-academy, and workshops in the area of agricultural development, aiming at enhancing partner countries’ institutional capacity and designing potential ODA projects
